Definition: Explicit statement about declining the dispense request (prescription), usually recorded in order to communicate the issue back to the prescriber. Reasons for declining a dispense may vary, but typically this statement is only sent when a following action is expected on the prescriberâ€™s side (cancelling or changing the problematic prescription or the whole treatment).

Short: Header level metadata about the dispense decline.
Definition: Header level metadata about the dispense decline.

Short: Patient who the medication was prescribed to. [Used for searching]
The person who dispensed the product, and takes the responsibility of the dispensation or declining the dispense. [Used for searching]
Definition: Author(s) by whom the resource was/were authored. Multiple authors could be provided.

Short: The time of recording the dispense or declining the request. [Used for searching]
Definition: Date and time of the issuing the document/resource by its author.

Short: Date and time of the last update to the resource
Definition: Date and time of the last update to the document/information
